title: Angular anisotropy of fragments from fission of Pu-242 by 0.10 - 6.38 MeV neutrons

x4freetext: Angular anisotropy of fragments from fission of Pu-242
by 0.10 - 6.38 MeV neutrons
Anisotropy data table. Issue 3.

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Soviet Journal of Nuclear Physics, Vol.52, p.419 (1990)

x4freetext: Engl.transl.of J,YF,52,650,1990
Electrostatic accelerators EG-1 , EG-2.5
Tandem accelerator KG-2.5
Monochromatic neutrons.
Cylindrical glass plates for fission fragments
detection.
Multiangle 4PI detector ( 10 angles - 4.5, 11.5,
Plutonium oxide Pu-O2, Pu-242 content is 96.7 % ,
Pu-240 content is 1.8 % , Pu-241 content is 0.32 % ,
Pu-239 content is 0.15 % ,Pu-238 content is 0.11 %
No information
Correction on fission of admixtures isotopes - 1.5 % ,
Correction on experimental hall background - 2 % ,
Correction on (p,n) reaction 2 % ,
Correction on layer inhomogeneity 1 % ,
Correction on (d,n) reaction 2.8 % .
